Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Offered for sale by Registration of Interest due Thursday 21st March 2013.

Part of a highly regarded Eyre Peninsula property portfolio this aggregation is located approximately 11km East of Darke Peak or 35km Northwest of Cleve in the Central Eyre Peninsula. Annual rainfall of 325mm with red/brown loamy soils to brown/grey sands farmed using minimum till practices.

The majority of the aggregation has been clay spread and/or delved. Improving grain production.
"Carrapee View" Total 1,640 Ha (4,052.4 acres) with approximately 1,044 Ha (2,579.7 acres) well cleared and arable.
"Teegan's" Total 885.0 Ha (2,186.8 acres) with approximately 752.0 Ha (1,858.1 acres) well cleared and arable.
"Sugarloaf" Total 568.0 Ha (1,404.2 acres) with approximately 503.0 Ha (1,242.9 acres) well cleared and arable.

"Nobles" 555.0 Ha (1,371.4 acres) with 541.6 Ha* (1,338.3 acres*) cleared and arable.
Located 18km northeast of Darke Peak on the eastern Eyre Peninsula, 45km northwest of Cleve Township. This medium sized property is mostly undulating to slightly hilly open red sandy loamy soils over clay with some lighter sands being typical swale farming soils in a 315mm average annual rainfall. In recent years most of the lighter sandy have been clayed improving soil structure and production ability.
The fencing is in good condition with some new fences of cyclone and wooden posts and the property is laid out into 5 paddocks. A well-maintained unsealed road leads to the property and well serviced roads throughout the property have been constructed for road train access.
2 SA Water meters service the property with mostly new piping and Tumby concrete troughs in all paddocks.
Noble's is farming land only, being a very well maintained farm with good modern minimum tillage farming program implemented in recent years. With a district average of 1.2t/Ha mainly APW wheat varieties and a legume break in the rotation this farm is well setup to move in and run a mixed farming enterprise. The 2012 season Noble's was planted down to lupins which provide the opportunity for an astute purchaser to come in with wheat for 2013 season.

The Eyre Peninsula is a reputable agricultural district and is recognised for its secure medium rainfall and large scale production capacity for dryland cropping and sheep enterprises.

“Pindari” is located approximately 152 radial kilometres north of Port Lincoln.  Port Lincoln is the primary regional centre for the area and services South Australia’s West Coast and Eyre Peninsula. The city also includes a deep sea port servicing panama vessels.

• 1,385.56Ha* over Two Freehold Titles
• 40km* north east of Cleve
• 3 bedroom home, 2 stand shearing shed with yards, fertiliser shed, machinery shed, chemical shed and silos
• Undulating land comprising quality red/brown sandy loam over clay
• Production history available
• Well fenced and sub-divided into 10 paddocks
• Average Rainfall 350mm* per annum
• Efficient access to Darke Peak, Cleve and Kimba grain receival sites

Inspections are only available upon appointment with the marketing agent.
The properties are being offered for sale by Public Auction.

Auction will be held on Friday 14th March 2014 at 11:00am.
Venue: Cleve Golf Club, Cleve.
Registration is required on the day.
* Approximate
